The paper deals with a combinatorial algorithm for the maximum weight stable matching problem, which is a classic problem in both computer science and economics. The paper also introduces new structural and algorithmic results related to stable matchings, such as the sublattice of maximum weight stable matchings and the notion of macro-rotations. These topics are closely related to the fields of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG).
